# Godot 4.6.1 Conventions

## Node Architecture
- Ships are `CharacterBody2D` with manual velocity (NOT RigidBody2D)
- Use composition: attach components as child nodes, not deep inheritance trees
- Prefer `@onready` over `_ready()` for node references
- Use `class_name` for any script referenced by other systems

## Signals
- Define signals at the top of the script, right after `class_name`
- Custom signals use past tense for events (`health_changed`, `weapon_fired`)
- Connect signals in `_ready()`, disconnect in `_exit_tree()` if connecting to singletons
- Cross-system signals go on `GameEventBus.gd`, not on individual nodes

## Common Godot 4.x Pitfalls
- `move_and_slide()` returns void in 4.x — use `get_last_motion()` and `get_slide_collision()` after
- `@export` vars aren't set yet in `_init()` — use `_ready()` for initialization that depends on exports
- `preload()` fails silently if the path is wrong — verify paths exist
- `JSON.parse_string()` returns `null` on failure, not an error — always check the return value
- `CharacterBody2D.velocity` is set before calling `move_and_slide()`, not passed as an argument
- Physics runs at a fixed rate — use `_physics_process()` for movement, `_process()` for visuals
- `delta` in `_physics_process()` is fixed; `delta` in `_process()` varies

## Performance Patterns
- Use object pools for anything spawned frequently (projectiles, particles, debris)
- Avoid `get_node()` in `_process()` / `_physics_process()` — cache references in `_ready()`
- `is_instance_valid()` before accessing nodes that might have been freed
- Disable `_process()` / `_physics_process()` on nodes that don't need per-frame updates
- Use `call_deferred()` for node tree modifications during physics callbacks

## File Naming
- Scripts: `snake_case.gd` matching the node they attach to
- Scenes: `PascalCase.tscn` matching the root node name
- Resources: `snake_case.tres`
- Folders: `snake_case/`
